1138
01:33:47,526 --> 01:33:49,585
your son, Lt. KarI MueIIer...

1139
01:33:49,695 --> 01:33:52,721
commanding a motor torpedo boat
off the French coast...

1140
01:33:52,798 --> 01:33:55,790
having sunk his fifth ship
in the Iast three months...

1141
01:33:55,901 --> 01:34:00,031
the Iatest, a soIo dayIight attack
which sank the British vesseI Carapace...

1142
01:34:00,106 --> 01:34:01,733
awarded the Knight's Cross.

1143
01:34:01,807 --> 01:34:03,866
-Wonderful.
-Congratulations, sir.

1144
01:34:03,943 --> 01:34:05,035
This is a great moment.

1145
01:34:05,111 --> 01:34:08,569
lt's only fitting to say, sir, that everyone
in your command feels honored.

1146
01:34:08,648 --> 01:34:10,707
That's very kind of you, Mr. Kruse.
Thank you.

1147
01:34:11,550 --> 01:34:14,246
The Carapace.
Let's see what's her tonnage.

1148
01:34:14,320 --> 01:34:15,810
lt must be in the Talbot.

1149
01:34:15,921 --> 01:34:18,788
Congratulations, Captain.
lt must be a proud moment.

1150
01:34:18,891 --> 01:34:19,949
Thank you, Mr. Keil.

1151
01:34:20,059 --> 01:34:21,219
Come in, gentlemen.

1152
01:34:21,994 --> 01:34:23,461
Congratulations, Captain.

1153
01:34:24,096 --> 01:34:26,394
-Congratulations.
-lt's wonderful.

1154
01:34:29,101 --> 01:34:32,400
-Carapace on Page 131, sir.
-To your health, sir.

1155
01:34:32,505 --> 01:34:34,405
-Good luck, Captain.
-And to your son.

1156
01:34:34,473 --> 01:34:35,599
To your health, sir.

1157
01:34:35,675 --> 01:34:37,302
He must be quite a seaman.

1158
01:34:51,257 --> 01:34:52,451
HeiI Hitler!

1159
01:34:53,125 --> 01:34:54,615
HeiI! HeiI!

1160
01:35:00,599 --> 01:35:02,624
Hail the Knight's Cross.

1161
01:35:06,972 --> 01:35:08,940
He's a crazy drunk.

1162
01:35:14,480 --> 01:35:15,504
HeiI!

1163
01:35:15,648 --> 01:35:17,616
-Half the ship can hear you.
-Can they?

1164
01:35:17,683 --> 01:35:20,880
Tell me about the consequences.
Tell me the consequences.

1165
01:35:22,455 --> 01:35:24,013
Read me the sentence.

1166
01:35:25,624 --> 01:35:27,353
What is the worst?

1167
01:35:27,560 --> 01:35:29,892
To fight war alongside you!

1168
01:35:32,064 --> 01:35:33,395
Milkereit...

1169
01:35:34,500 --> 01:35:36,468
you poor fool.

1170
01:35:36,535 --> 01:35:38,901
Raised your voice against them.

1171
01:35:39,572 --> 01:35:42,336
You don't know about the consequences.

1172
01:35:50,349 --> 01:35:52,044
Wouldn't it be wonderful...

1173
01:35:52,151 --> 01:35:55,416
if it turned out
you're not an SS man at all?

1174
01:36:05,197 --> 01:36:08,064
Oh, they will turn you into one of them...

1175
01:36:08,567 --> 01:36:10,228
into a cannibal.

1176
01:36:13,272 --> 01:36:17,436
The most wonderful, gentle boy....

1177
01:36:20,846 --> 01:36:22,507
HeiI cannibals!

1178
01:36:24,517 --> 01:36:25,609
HeiI!

1179
01:36:26,218 --> 01:36:27,242
HeiI!

1180
01:36:29,722 --> 01:36:31,781
Take your stations. Everybody.

1181
01:36:31,957 --> 01:36:33,447
Come with me.

1182
01:36:33,559 --> 01:36:35,891
Tell all the officers to assemble
in the salon at once.

1183
01:36:35,961 --> 01:36:37,019
Yes, sir.

1184
01:36:37,630 --> 01:36:41,396
The point we spoke about.
lt's here, and l need you as a witness.

1185
01:36:48,407 --> 01:36:49,567
Now, go on.

1186
01:37:04,056 --> 01:37:06,115
Things are falling apart.

1187
01:37:06,592 --> 01:37:08,389
Keil can't do it.

1188
01:37:09,628 --> 01:37:10,890
l will.

1189
01:37:15,835 --> 01:37:18,998
Sure, he is on a spree, but he'll work it off.

1190
01:37:20,172 --> 01:37:22,800
l've made this entry in the ship's diary.

1191
01:37:22,908 --> 01:37:26,344
''Capt. Mueller is mentally
and physically irresponsible...

1192
01:37:26,445 --> 01:37:29,073
''due to alcoholic over-indulgence.''

1193
01:37:29,248 --> 01:37:30,977
Dr. Ambach will confirm this.

1194
01:37:31,517 --> 01:37:34,145
l wouldn't take coke-head's diagnosis
of a cockroach.

1195
01:37:34,253 --> 01:37:37,188
Mr. Branner, Mueller's illness is chronic.

1196
01:37:37,957 --> 01:37:40,790
He was drunk
when his last ship was torpedoed.

1197
01:37:41,927 --> 01:37:43,827
lt's hard to believe.

1198
01:37:43,996 --> 01:37:45,327
Mr. Keil?

1199
01:37:45,865 --> 01:37:46,923
Yeah.

1200
01:37:47,366 --> 01:37:50,130
lt's unfortunate, but he is correct.

1201
01:37:51,303 --> 01:37:55,364
And under the circumstances, l think
we must follow Mr. Kruse.

1202
01:37:58,177 --> 01:38:01,977
For the protection of the ship,
l am now taking command.

1203
01:38:02,948 --> 01:38:05,314
lnform your men. Dismissed.

1204
01:38:05,384 --> 01:38:06,544
Capt. Kruse?

1205
01:38:06,652 --> 01:38:08,950
Captain, it's for my health.

1206
01:38:09,021 --> 01:38:11,888
Mueller didn't understand this.
l can't live without it.

1207
01:38:11,991 --> 01:38:14,482
l'll see you get what you need,
but it won't be morphine.

1208
01:38:17,563 --> 01:38:20,862
This one here was caught trying to sneak
into the prisoners' hatch.

1209
01:38:21,166 --> 01:38:22,394
Really?

1210
01:38:22,568 --> 01:38:25,196
Well, perhaps that's where
she prefers to be.

1211
01:38:29,074 --> 01:38:31,565
Take her down in the hold with the others.

1212
01:38:36,916 --> 01:38:37,974
Go ahead.

1213
01:38:40,319 --> 01:38:43,811
l don't mean to interfere,
but this is disgusting.

1214
01:38:43,923 --> 01:38:45,720
Thank you very much
for your help, Mr. Keil.

1215
01:38:45,824 --> 01:38:46,848
Yeah.

1216
01:38:54,033 --> 01:38:55,762
-Steward?
-Yes, sir.

1217
01:38:56,368 --> 01:38:59,826
-l have been told that you are now--
-Correct. Here.

1218
01:39:00,205 --> 01:39:02,537
Sew the fourth stripe on the sleeve.

1219
01:39:02,608 --> 01:39:04,098
-lt's regulations.
-Yes, sir.

1220
01:39:34,406 --> 01:39:36,237
lf this works out...

1221
01:39:37,242 --> 01:39:41,542
l want a front row seat
when we nail Kruse to the mast.

1222
01:39:43,148 --> 01:39:45,207
-Are the men ready?
-Yes.

1223
01:39:45,584 --> 01:39:46,608
They will be.

1224
01:39:47,653 --> 01:39:50,747
But suppose the girl can't persuade
those prisoners?

1225
01:39:50,823 --> 01:39:53,587
Then l'll have to try to get down there
when the watch changes...

1226
01:39:53,659 --> 01:39:55,149
and persuade them myself.

1227
01:39:56,228 --> 01:39:58,822
All right, but that will be a while.

1228
01:39:59,298 --> 01:40:01,789
Suppose we believe this guy Keil.

1229
01:40:02,134 --> 01:40:03,761
What's his plan?

1230
01:40:03,836 --> 01:40:05,736
You start a fire down here.

1231
01:40:05,804 --> 01:40:06,998
Then you scream your lungs out.

1232
01:40:07,106 --> 01:40:09,438
You climb up the ladder,
and when you get to the top...

1233
01:40:09,508 --> 01:40:10,668
you yell, run, and scatter.

1234
01:40:10,776 --> 01:40:12,334
Are you kidding, lady?

1235
01:40:12,444 --> 01:40:15,106
They'll be waiting up there
to shoot us full of holes.

1236
01:40:15,180 --> 01:40:18,809
No. The fire will confuse the guards,
and Keil's men will overcome them.

1237
01:40:18,917 --> 01:40:22,250
Honey, you can't win a battle
just by yelling. You need guns.

1238
01:40:22,421 --> 01:40:23,820
We'll get guns.

1239
01:40:23,922 --> 01:40:26,152
Guns, guns.
Where are they gonna get guns?

1240
01:40:26,258 --> 01:40:27,850
One of the officers is with us.

1241
01:40:27,960 --> 01:40:30,622
He'll attack the captain and take the keys
to the ordnance room.

1242
01:40:30,696 --> 01:40:34,029
The whole stunt's cockeyed.
Let them try it alone.

1243
01:40:34,433 --> 01:40:36,663
They're outnumbered. lt's nine against 40.

1244
01:40:36,769 --> 01:40:37,963
So?

1245
01:40:38,037 --> 01:40:41,973
So we join them, huh?
And then it's only 2-to-1 against us.

1246
01:40:42,041 --> 01:40:43,099
That's enough.

1247
01:40:44,676 --> 01:40:47,008
Let's suppose we make this Keil circle.

1248
01:40:47,112 --> 01:40:50,309
We get a cup of coffee
and a first class ticket to the Golden Gate.

1249
01:40:50,449 --> 01:40:53,213
-Then what?
-Then we get good and drunk.

1250
01:40:54,386 --> 01:40:56,354
Sleep for a month, huh?
Get a bath tub of beer.

1251
01:40:56,455 --> 01:40:59,686
We'll see if the girls
are still at Shany's bar.

1252
01:40:59,792 --> 01:41:01,384
That's for me. l say aye.

1253
01:41:01,493 --> 01:41:02,892
Well, don't be such a hero.

1254
01:41:02,995 --> 01:41:05,691
You'll get a kiss and a drink
and two weeks shore leave.

1255
01:41:05,798 --> 01:41:07,959
And after that, you'll be back
on the frontlines again.

1256
01:41:08,033 --> 01:41:10,365
Swimming in burning oil
and boiling like a mackerel.

1257
01:41:10,469 --> 01:41:12,630
l say, let's vote on it. And l'm for it.

1258
01:41:12,704 --> 01:41:14,831
-l'm with you.
-Good man. What do you say?

1259
01:41:14,907 --> 01:41:15,965
l'll go along, fellas.

1260
01:41:16,041 --> 01:41:17,508
-Okay.
-That's it. Come on, huh?

1261
01:41:17,576 --> 01:41:20,409
-All right, l'm in.
-Ten, huh?

1262
01:41:20,512 --> 01:41:22,002
-Against five.
-Majority rules.

1263
01:41:22,081 --> 01:41:23,742
-Yeah.
-The hell it does.

1264
01:41:23,849 --> 01:41:25,009
This ain't the Congress.

1265
01:41:25,084 --> 01:41:27,575
-Okay, man. Then we'll try it without you.
-The hell you will.

1266
01:41:27,686 --> 01:41:29,210
You blow this, and they'll kill us all.

1267
01:41:29,321 --> 01:41:30,345
That's not true.

1268
01:41:30,422 --> 01:41:32,982
Come on. Do you think those bastards
will string you up...

1269
01:41:33,058 --> 01:41:35,151
and serve us ice cream
just because we laid off?

1270
01:41:35,227 --> 01:41:36,854
-Listen--
-Start a fire here...

1271
01:41:36,929 --> 01:41:39,420
and they'll be damn sure
every one of us is in on it.

1272
01:41:39,531 --> 01:41:40,555
He's right.

1273
01:41:44,169 --> 01:41:45,830
Look, l'm sorry.

1274
01:41:46,105 --> 01:41:48,266
We'd take the chance, you see...

1275
01:41:49,541 --> 01:41:51,168
but it'd have to be all of us.

1276
01:41:52,444 --> 01:41:54,844
l'd rather take my chances
in a prison camp.

1277
01:41:54,913 --> 01:41:57,108
Hell, l'd like to take mine right here.

1278
01:41:57,216 --> 01:41:58,877
-You and me both.
-Sure.

1279
01:41:58,951 --> 01:42:02,250
Don't look so worried, baby.
We're all nice guys.

1280
01:42:02,788 --> 01:42:03,846
Sure.

1281
01:42:04,089 --> 01:42:07,081
You kept too much to yourself
on the old BIue DoIphin.

1282
01:42:07,192 --> 01:42:10,127
lf you'd spent a little time with us,
you might have had some fun.

1283
01:42:10,229 --> 01:42:13,255
And, baby, we've got nothing but time
from now on.

1284
01:42:13,365 --> 01:42:15,026
Are you kidding? Get your hands back.

1285
01:42:23,976 --> 01:42:26,035
There's one thing you're good for.

1286
01:42:31,216 --> 01:42:32,740
Stop it. Break it up.

1287
01:42:38,323 --> 01:42:40,553
You can have it if you want it.

1288
01:42:54,106 --> 01:42:55,232
And you.

1289
01:42:56,909 --> 01:42:59,139
Or you. Join the others.

1290
01:43:08,820 --> 01:43:10,845
Make them keep their word.

1291
01:43:12,591 --> 01:43:14,081
Make them keep it.

1292
01:46:39,231 --> 01:46:41,358
-Mr. Kruse?
-Yeah?

1293
01:46:43,969 --> 01:46:46,563
Sir, a radio message from Adm. Wendel.

1294
01:46:46,671 --> 01:46:47,797
Wendel?

1295
01:46:57,549 --> 01:46:58,982
Thank you.

1296
01:47:03,722 --> 01:47:06,657
l'll handle the so-called Mr. Keil.

1297
01:47:12,164 --> 01:47:14,098
Milkereit! Milkereit!

1298
01:47:27,913 --> 01:47:32,247
Now you will kindly tell me
what this is all about.

1299
01:47:38,290 --> 01:47:40,349
l can start a new one now.

1300
01:47:40,525 --> 01:47:41,787
You see?

1301
01:47:42,861 --> 01:47:44,294
lt's very nice.

1302
01:47:49,434 --> 01:47:50,594
Yes. Branner.

1303
01:48:24,402 --> 01:48:25,801
Fire! Fire!

1304
01:48:26,938 --> 01:48:28,838
Brandt, come with me.

1305
01:48:29,007 --> 01:48:31,100
Lutz, you cover them.

1306
01:48:33,745 --> 01:48:35,679
Donkeyman, the ordnance room.

1307
01:49:08,313 --> 01:49:09,541
Surrender!

1308
01:49:09,648 --> 01:49:11,013
All right! All right!

1309
01:49:11,116 --> 01:49:13,346
We give up here. Don't shoot.

1310
01:49:15,554 --> 01:49:17,146
We are finished.

1311
01:49:24,529 --> 01:49:25,723
Come up.

1312
01:49:31,503 --> 01:49:33,198
Up. Get in line.

1313
01:50:07,872 --> 01:50:09,237
All right.

1314
01:50:09,941 --> 01:50:12,501
Let's find the other two. Branner?

1315
01:50:13,111 --> 01:50:15,705
Mr. Branner, take the engine room.

1316
01:50:16,014 --> 01:50:17,447
Cornelson, the foredeck.

1317
01:50:21,553 --> 01:50:24,181
There is a rubber boat.

1318
01:50:24,255 --> 01:50:25,620
Midships.

1319
01:50:26,758 --> 01:50:30,057
We can heave it over the side
and jump after it.

1320
01:50:30,695 --> 01:50:33,095
We'll disappear in two minutes.

1321
01:50:35,367 --> 01:50:36,698
Come on.

1322
01:50:37,569 --> 01:50:39,127
We can make it.

1323
01:50:41,206 --> 01:50:42,434
Why not?

1324
01:50:47,045 --> 01:50:49,138
Now l blow up the ship.

1325
01:50:56,154 --> 01:50:57,382
Do it.

1326
01:51:11,169 --> 01:51:12,966
Anybody seen my bird?

1327
01:51:13,071 --> 01:51:14,766
l can't find him.

1328
01:51:16,074 --> 01:51:18,508
My baby hates the sound of guns.

1329
01:51:19,177 --> 01:51:20,769
Scares the feathers off him.

1330
01:51:22,480 --> 01:51:23,606
Where's Keil?

1331
01:51:28,420 --> 01:51:30,115
Where's Keil?

1332
01:51:30,388 --> 01:51:31,480
Keil?

1333
01:51:34,559 --> 01:51:35,992
Where's Keil?

1334
01:51:40,465 --> 01:51:41,727
Where's Keil?

1335
01:51:42,901 --> 01:51:45,131
He is hiding in the propeller shaft.

1336
01:51:45,937 --> 01:51:46,961
Move!

1337
01:51:47,172 --> 01:51:48,969
-Take the prisoners below.
-Yes, sir.

1338
01:53:02,580 --> 01:53:04,411
Search the lifeboats.

1339
01:54:12,083 --> 01:54:13,744
Capt. Mueller?

1340
01:54:15,553 --> 01:54:17,885
-So Adm. Wendel was right.
-Yeah.

1341
01:54:18,890 --> 01:54:20,653
But there is no time for this.

1342
01:54:21,559 --> 01:54:22,890
Why not?

1343
01:54:23,628 --> 01:54:26,153
-Your mutiny has failed.
-Not yet.

1344
01:54:26,564 --> 01:54:28,429
You once said that...

1345
01:54:29,601 --> 01:54:32,399
the worst consequence would be
to have to fight...

1346
01:54:32,470 --> 01:54:34,563
alongside men like Kruse.

1347
01:54:34,839 --> 01:54:35,999
There is another way.

1348
01:54:36,241 --> 01:54:39,802
There is a rendezvous point where
American warships are waiting for us...

1349
01:54:39,911 --> 01:54:43,108
at 14 degrees North, 175 degrees East.

1350
01:54:44,015 --> 01:54:45,778
You have a choice.

1351
01:54:48,319 --> 01:54:50,844
Whatever else l am, l'm not a traitor.

1352
01:54:52,323 --> 01:54:54,188
Neither was your son.

1353
01:54:59,364 --> 01:55:02,458
Get out. Get out.

1354
01:55:03,134 --> 01:55:04,999
Yeah, l will.

1355
01:55:09,641 --> 01:55:11,268
There! On the bridge!

1356
01:55:12,710 --> 01:55:14,143
Out! Get out!

1357
01:55:14,212 --> 01:55:15,304
Move!

1358
01:55:18,316 --> 01:55:19,442
No.

1359
01:55:19,617 --> 01:55:21,016
Mr. Keil, please, don't.

1360
01:55:47,845 --> 01:55:50,040
The engine room is torn to pieces.

1361
01:55:50,214 --> 01:55:51,681
She's flooding.

1362
01:55:51,983 --> 01:55:53,007
Abandon ship.

1363
01:55:56,387 --> 01:55:58,150
Abandon ship!

1364
01:56:01,993 --> 01:56:03,858
Abandon ship!

1365
01:56:05,596 --> 01:56:06,995
Hurry up!

1366
01:56:16,240 --> 01:56:17,502
Hurry up!

1367
01:56:23,915 --> 01:56:25,075
Here.

1368
01:56:27,552 --> 01:56:28,917
Over here.

1369
01:56:29,220 --> 01:56:30,687
But, sir, please--

1370
01:56:30,755 --> 01:56:34,191
Now l am where l belong.
l intend to stay here.

1371
01:56:34,359 --> 01:56:36,259
Now over the side, all of you.

1372
01:56:41,632 --> 01:56:43,759
-Captain.
-Do as l say.

1373
01:57:43,094 --> 01:57:44,493
Mr. Kruse!

1374
01:57:45,329 --> 01:57:46,694
Over here!

1375
01:57:49,600 --> 01:57:50,624
Over here!

1376
01:58:01,112 --> 01:58:02,306
Here.

1377
01:58:04,816 --> 01:58:06,215
Come on, Mr. Kruse.

1378
01:58:06,951 --> 01:58:08,350
Over here.

1379
01:58:58,169 --> 01:58:59,830
Capt. Mueller.

1380
01:59:44,315 --> 01:59:45,714
Mr. Keil?

1381
01:59:47,451 --> 01:59:49,476
You won't need that raft for a while.

1382
01:59:49,587 --> 01:59:51,282
But what is it?

1383
01:59:52,623 --> 01:59:54,284
What's happened?

1384
01:59:54,492 --> 01:59:55,754
Well...

1385
01:59:57,161 --> 02:00:00,324
the lard. lt solidified.

1386
02:00:00,831 --> 02:00:02,423
Plugged up the hole.

1387
02:00:02,500 --> 02:00:05,298
How much longer will we remain afloat?

1388
02:00:05,803 --> 02:00:08,067
Well, it's lasted two hours.

1389
02:00:09,440 --> 02:00:12,068
Maybe another two, maybe 10...

1390
02:00:12,810 --> 02:00:14,505
unless we break up first.

1391
02:00:17,481 --> 02:00:18,914
Ten hours.

1392
02:00:23,354 --> 02:00:25,914
ln what direction are we drifting?

1393
02:00:27,758 --> 02:00:30,318
We couldn't drift that far in days.

1394
02:00:30,595 --> 02:00:34,326
lt would take a warship going full ahead
a good six or seven hours.

1395
02:00:34,432 --> 02:00:36,161
Capt. Mueller...

1396
02:00:37,501 --> 02:00:42,302
l don't suppose you would consider
sending a radio message for me?

1397
02:00:45,009 --> 02:00:47,534
You're not very subtle, Mr. Keil.

1398
02:00:49,013 --> 02:00:51,174
But l must admire your courage.

1399
02:00:52,149 --> 02:00:54,845
You're the one with courage, Mueller.

1400
02:00:57,722 --> 02:00:59,451
lt takes real courage...

1401
02:01:00,625 --> 02:01:03,958
to see your son
turn into a merciless fanatic...

1402
02:01:07,198 --> 02:01:10,690
and still believe in your mildewed
concepts of the fatherland.

1403
02:01:13,738 --> 02:01:15,171
l envy you.

1404
02:01:15,506 --> 02:01:18,066
l wish l had so much to believe in.

1405
02:01:23,247 --> 02:01:26,978
lf you have nothing to believe in,
why did you blow up the ship?

1406
02:01:31,522 --> 02:01:33,752
That doesn't matter now.

1407
02:03:10,888 --> 02:03:11,855
English

